    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "Omaha, Neb. --\nNate McHugh\ndelivered four hits, including a two-run blast to put Creighton ahead, as Bluejay Baseball defeated Omaha 8-2 on Wednesday, March 18.\nThe victory pushed Creighton to 9-8 on the season, while Omaha fell to 7-11.\nOmaha took an early 1-0 in the top of the second as Hayden Lewis blasted a solo home run over the center field wall. The Mavericks extended their edge to 2-0 on an RBI single from Henry Zipay in the third.\nCreighton responded with two runs in the third, loading the bags on a walk to\nTeddy Deters\n, a single from McHugh and a walk to\nIsaac Wachsmann\n.\nJoe Washburn\npaid off the opportunity with an RBI single to third, while an errant throw tied the contest as McHugh scampered across.\nTwo innings later Deters drew his third walk of the game, then McHugh blasted his fifth home run of the season to put Creighton up 4-2.\nThe Bluejays tacked on four runs in the seventh, pushing across four runs on three hits and two walks. The inning began with a walk to Deters and a single from McHugh. One out later Wachsmann drew the Bluejays' eighth free pass of the game to load the bases.\nNick Venteicher\nfollowed with an RBI single to right field, then\nConnor Capece\nlaced a two-run single to left-center and\nNick Bowron\nlifted a sacrifice fly to center to give Creighton an 8-2 edge.\nBrian Gould\nearned the win (1-0), tossing 2.2 innings of scoreless relief. Omaha reliever Brayden Curtis took the loss (1-1), allowing two runs on three hits.\nCreighton heads out to Miami on Thursday morning as the Bluejays open a three-game series against the Miami Hurricanes on Friday, March 20 at 6:00 pm.\nDETAILS TO COME!"
